Zing Wells Automation – Selenium + PyTest (Hybrid Framework)
This project automates key workflows of the Zing Wells web application using Selenium WebDriver and Python, implemented with a Hybrid Automation Framework (POM + Data‑Driven + Keyword‑Driven).
It is designed to be maintainable, scalable, and easy to extend for regression testing.

🔑 Key Features

Selenium + Python automation
Hybrid Framework (POM + Data/Data Utilities + Keywords)
PyTest runner with fixtures
HTML reporting
Screenshots on failures
Console logging support
Tag‑based test execution


📁 Project Structure (Simple Overview)
/tests            → Test cases  
/pages            → Page Object Model classes  
/utilities        → Helper methods (browser, logger, config, data)  
/testdata         → Test input files  
/reports          → HTML reports & logs  
conftest.py       → Browser setup + fixtures  
requirements.txt  → Dependencies list


▶ Running the Project
1️⃣ Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

2️⃣ Run all tests
pytestShow more lines

3️⃣ Run tests with console logs
py -m pytest -v -sShow more lines

4️⃣ Run tests with specific marker (example: task2)
pytest -m task2Show more lines

5️⃣ Generate HTML report
pytest --html=report.htmlShow more lines

6️⃣ Run HTML report + console logs together
py -m pytest -v -s --html=report.htmlShow more lines

7️⃣ Run tests in parallel (if xdist installed)
pytest -n 3Show more lines
